related_questions.question: What does organic search mean?
related_questions.snippet: Organic search is a method for entering one or several search terms as a single string of text into a search engine. Organic search results appear as paginated lists, are based on relevance to the search terms, and exclude advertisements; whereas non-organic search results do not filter out pay per click advertising.
